Description:
Cornelisz Engelbrechtsz or Jan de Cock. The Procession to Calvary, Panel 12 1/8 x 16 7/8 inches, Yale University Art Gallery New Haven, Connecticut. Cornelis Engelbrechtsz. (Leyden) trained 3 sons as well as Aertgen & Lucas van Leyden. Jan de Cock (Jan van Leyden) must sometime have been associated with Cornelis'circle; De Cock is known to have worked in Antwerp...[sic] Sirén attributed this picture to Engelbrechtsz., Friedländer (tentatively) Winkler & Held to Jan de Cock. Hoogewerff ascribed it to a son of Engelbrechtsz., Lucas Cornelisz., while Valentiner has suggested the name of another of the painter's sons, Cornelis Cornelisz.Kunst by whom van Mander knew a Christ Carrying the Cross. Held has shown that a larger version of the present painting once existed and was apparently very famous as it is pursued in several early copies and variants. 
[Osvald] SIRÉN, A Descriptive Catalogue of the Pictures in the Jarves Collection belonging to Yale University, New Haven [Yale University Press] 1916, pp. 271-272, ill.; FRIEDLÄNDER, XI, 1934, pp. 65, 126, N°13; [Friedrich] WINKLER, Die altniederländische Malerei, [Berlin: Propylaën-Verlag](1924), p. 214; J.S. HELD, [Notizen zu einem niederländischen Skizzenbuch in Berlin], Oud-Holland, 2, 1933, pp. 276, 280 ill.; G.J. Hoogewerff, De Noord-Nederlandsche schilderkunst, III, ['s-Gravenhage: Nijhoff](1939), pp. 371-72; [W.R.] VALENTINER, Notes on the So-Called Jan de Cock, Art Quarterly, XIII (1950), p. 62, ill. 
For earlier compositions of the similar type school of Patinir with L. Harris, London, publ. by F.C. Willis, in Monatshefte für Kunstwissenschaft 1914, Taf. 11. and ebd., Taf. 13, school of Patinir, München Freiherr von Schacky, a Cornelis Massys, Karlsruhe Coll. A. Meier, publ. by F. Winkler, [= Eine heilige Familie von Cornelis Massys], Cicerone 1929/21, [pp. 401-403], p. 401. (Hier geht der Zug von rechts nach links u. im Gans verschieden von Bruegel;[kantlijn][toegevoegde vermelding]: 'Look up print by Lucas van Leyden with Virgin & St. John separated.'; [verso] [Briefhoofd University of Cambridge. Board of Extra-Mural Studies] d.d. 11/10/1954: Korte inhoud: National Insurance Part-time Lectures & Tutors. Ondertekend door G.F. Hickson.

Keyword: New Haven, Yale University Art Gallery
